nhc_headline: ...HUMBERTO HAS MERGED WITH A FRONT... ...THIS IS THE LAST ADVISORY... ...DANGEROUS SURF AND RIP CURRENTS TO CONTINUE ACROSS THE WESTERN ATLANTIC COASTLINE THROUGH THE WEEK...
summary: ...HUMBERTO HAS MERGED WITH A FRONT... ...THIS IS THE LAST ADVISORY... ...DANGEROUS SURF AND RIP CURRENTS TO CONTINUE ACROSS THE WESTERN ATLANTIC COASTLINE THROUGH THE WEEK... As of 11:00 AM AST Wed Oct 01 the center of Humberto was located near 37.0, -63.0 with movement ENE at 23 mph. The minimum central pressure was 980 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 70 mph.
